review_blob: This is not your average ipa. Lacks the full ipa bite, but has a distinctive, sweet, subtle flavor that complexes nices with the hops. Could be a liitle bit more bitter, butthis is the best ipa Ive ever had. Thats saying a lot. Could be a little bit more adventerous, but doesnt overpower the hops like a lot of pale brews.

Excellent dark color. Medium head that lasts for a decent while. Aroma gives an earthy, malty scent. 
 Taste similar to that of Shiner Bock minus the often skunky feature plus more of the signature yeasty maltiness. 
 Definite improvement over Shiner Bock.

Poured dark brown into glass with long lasting multi layered head.  Aroma fueled by carbs, yeasty and chocolaty. Sediment suspended in fluid. Bitter taste complexed with a medium sweetness from caramel, fruit, and malt. The alcohol content is very high, but is well layered into the flavors. A little too stouty for my taste. This is basically a much better produced/brewed 1554  Excellent beer, but I guess I prefer Chimays drinkability and slightly lighter bitterness.

Poured into glass. Thick head, stayed for awhile then fizzled. 
 Lots of carbonation. Caramel, chocolate, coffee, a little nuttiness. sublime sweet finish.
 Medium brown color, full body, almost creamy. 
 Pretty good beer. I was a little stuffy when I had it, but still came out well.
